1
00:00:55,054 --> 00:00:57,056
ALL CHARACTERS, PLACES,
ORGANIZATIONS, AND INCIDENTS

2
00:00:57,140 --> 00:00:58,683
PORTRAYED IN THIS DRAMA ARE FICTITIOUS

3
00:00:59,017 --> 00:01:01,227
EPISODE 10

4
00:01:03,688 --> 00:01:04,522
Enough.

5
00:01:05,899 --> 00:01:06,900
What?

6
00:01:09,611 --> 00:01:10,945
I want you to stop now.

7
00:01:13,323 --> 00:01:14,532
Stop what?

8
00:01:17,994 --> 00:01:20,080
RECORDING

9
00:01:20,163 --> 00:01:21,456
Let me see.

10
00:01:23,291 --> 00:01:25,210
Was it around here?

11
00:01:28,797 --> 00:01:32,675
The law is
all about disciplining the poor.

12
00:01:33,218 --> 00:01:35,804
The law doesn't apply to those who rule.

13
00:01:36,596 --> 00:01:39,516
So? Would you please
tell me about it in detail?

14
00:01:40,975 --> 00:01:41,935
It's nothing.

15
00:01:42,393 --> 00:01:43,394
It was an accident.

16
00:01:44,771 --> 00:01:46,689
I hit his dad with a car,

17
00:01:48,149 --> 00:01:49,192
and he died instantly.

18
00:01:50,819 --> 00:01:52,821
But someone else ended up in jail.
End of the story.

19
00:01:55,824 --> 00:01:57,033
What are you doing?

20
00:01:59,911 --> 00:02:01,621
I've never seen

21
00:02:02,247 --> 00:02:04,833
a dumbhead like you my whole life.

22
00:02:04,916 --> 00:02:06,334
Damn it.

23
00:02:15,051 --> 00:02:16,052
You see,

24
00:02:17,637 --> 00:02:20,014
I love my boss like crazy.

25
00:02:23,601 --> 00:02:24,602
But the problem is

26
00:02:25,854 --> 00:02:31,651
that his head is full of the bastards
from that damn Jangga Co.

27
00:02:35,572 --> 00:02:37,490
I'm so jealous.

28
00:02:42,245 --> 00:02:44,914
You damn sons of bitches.

29
00:02:58,386 --> 00:02:59,429
So

30
00:03:01,431 --> 00:03:03,641
I'm going to crush you all.

31
00:03:13,318 --> 00:03:14,277
Yi-seo.

32
00:03:14,861 --> 00:03:15,945
Jo Yi-seo!

33
00:03:22,869 --> 00:03:24,495
Hey, stop right there!

34
00:03:32,712 --> 00:03:33,880
I...

35
00:03:34,756 --> 00:03:35,757
clearly told you to stop.

36
00:03:37,216 --> 00:03:40,553
You're guilty of covering up a murder
and now even assault.

37
00:03:42,847 --> 00:03:44,182
Give me your phone.

38
00:03:44,974 --> 00:03:46,559
You'd better before I kill you.

39
00:03:47,977 --> 00:03:49,687
I said, give me your phone!

40
00:03:50,647 --> 00:03:53,441
You know what? We're in Itaewon now.

41
00:03:55,944 --> 00:03:57,028
Help!

42
00:04:09,874 --> 00:04:13,461
This area is filled with gentlemen
from all over the world.

43
00:04:17,507 --> 00:04:18,800
You're enjoying this.

44
00:04:20,301 --> 00:04:24,264
You see, people aren't fans
of uncertain situations.

45
00:04:25,723 --> 00:04:27,642
And if there's one thing
that always works...

46
00:04:28,726 --> 00:04:29,894
Watch, okay?

47
00:04:40,238 --> 00:04:41,155
You son of a bitch.

48
00:04:44,325 --> 00:04:45,535
Get it?

49
00:04:47,036 --> 00:04:48,871
In Itaewon,
or anywhere else for that matter,

50
00:04:48,955 --> 00:04:50,832
money solves all problems--

51
00:04:56,879 --> 00:04:57,714
Boss?

52
00:04:59,799 --> 00:05:01,217
What's going on?

53
00:05:01,801 --> 00:05:03,970
Why are you on the ground? Get up.

54
00:05:05,596 --> 00:05:09,058
Boss, I recorded everything.

55
00:05:09,142 --> 00:05:12,895
I recorded that bastard confessing
the murder of your father.

56
00:05:13,396 --> 00:05:16,649
If we use this and involve the media,
the police may reinvestigate the case.

57
00:05:20,153 --> 00:05:22,864
What happened to your face?

58
00:05:32,623 --> 00:05:35,418
Was it you? Did you do that to her face?

59
00:05:36,836 --> 00:05:37,670
Yes.

60
00:05:38,212 --> 00:05:39,047
What about it?

61
00:05:40,089 --> 00:05:42,133
You want to punch me? Go ahead.

62
00:05:42,633 --> 00:05:44,010
Punch me all you want.

63
00:05:44,635 --> 00:05:46,387
And get locked up again
for attempted murder.

64
00:05:46,471 --> 00:05:47,680
-You crazy--
-Boss.

65
00:05:50,975 --> 00:05:54,020
Don't be such a bluffer.
Go ahead and punch me.

66
00:05:54,604 --> 00:05:55,980
Boss.

67
00:05:56,939 --> 00:05:58,066
Don't.

68
00:06:15,291 --> 00:06:16,501
Shit.

69
00:06:21,172 --> 00:06:22,840
-Where are you going?
-Fuck, step aside.

70
00:06:23,341 --> 00:06:25,718
-Move. I said, step aside.
-Jeez!

71
00:06:34,102 --> 00:06:35,478
Damn it.

72
00:06:56,791 --> 00:06:57,834
Just let it go.

73
00:06:58,793 --> 00:06:59,919
It's all over now...

74
00:07:05,466 --> 00:07:06,467
It's over.

75
00:07:12,348 --> 00:07:13,558
Are you okay?

76
00:07:15,351 --> 00:07:17,687
Yes, I'm fine.
These things don't hurt at all.

77
00:07:18,396 --> 00:07:21,524
I saw you worrying about me
and getting angry for me. That's enough.

78
00:07:32,243 --> 00:07:33,077
Sorry.

79
00:07:36,289 --> 00:07:37,331
I'm sorry.

80
00:08:03,691 --> 00:08:05,568
WHAT HAPPENED TO MY BOSS TEN YEARS AGO

81
00:08:05,651 --> 00:08:08,946
Last night,
an assault was reported in Itaewon.

82
00:08:09,030 --> 00:08:11,491
It has been confirmed that the assailant
was Mr. Jang Geun-won,

83
00:08:11,574 --> 00:08:13,367
the son of Jangga's chairman,
Mr. Jang Dae-hee,

84
00:08:13,451 --> 00:08:15,203
who's been accused
of power abuse in the past.

85
00:08:15,286 --> 00:08:16,954
This assault case

86
00:08:17,038 --> 00:08:19,332
is taking a toll on public sentiment
toward the company.

87
00:08:19,790 --> 00:08:22,418
According to the assault victim, Ms. Jo,

88
00:08:22,502 --> 00:08:24,378
Mr. Jang lost his temper
because she recorded

89
00:08:24,462 --> 00:08:27,006
his confession about a hit-and-run
which he caused in the past.

90
00:08:27,089 --> 00:08:29,467
He couldn't control his anger
during their argument

91
00:08:29,550 --> 00:08:32,011
and brutally assaulted the victim.

92
00:08:35,681 --> 00:08:36,766
You idiot!

93
00:08:39,644 --> 00:08:40,603
I'm sorry.

94
00:08:44,649 --> 00:08:46,234
I told you to bring her on board.

95
00:08:47,026 --> 00:08:48,528
Why hit her?

96
00:08:53,074 --> 00:08:54,492
I'm really sorry.

97
00:08:56,619 --> 00:08:57,537
You moron.

98
00:08:59,997 --> 00:09:01,040
And what?

99
00:09:01,791 --> 00:09:03,417
You confessed to the hit-and-run?

100
00:09:13,135 --> 00:09:14,178
Get out.

101
00:09:15,972 --> 00:09:17,473
You don't even deserve a beating.

102
00:09:48,421 --> 00:09:49,755
God damn it!

103
00:10:01,183 --> 00:10:02,435
What are you doing here alone?

104
00:10:06,397 --> 00:10:07,481
Min-jung.

105
00:10:10,693 --> 00:10:12,570
I can't believe your father hit you.

106
00:10:12,695 --> 00:10:13,904
Let me take a look.

107
00:10:15,031 --> 00:10:16,282
Are you okay?

108
00:10:17,950 --> 00:10:19,410
I deserved it.

109
00:10:20,578 --> 00:10:21,662
Min-jung, I'm sorry for...

110
00:10:22,663 --> 00:10:23,497
I mean...

111
00:10:25,124 --> 00:10:27,710
Ms. Kang, I'm sorry for causing a mess.

112
00:10:28,544 --> 00:10:30,004
What you did was wrong,

113
00:10:30,546 --> 00:10:31,714
but what's done is done.

114
00:10:32,590 --> 00:10:35,259
You shouldn't look so dejected
as the future head of the company.

115
00:10:36,677 --> 00:10:37,595
Keep your chin up.

116
00:10:39,597 --> 00:10:40,806
The company will do everything

117
00:10:41,849 --> 00:10:42,892
to take care of it.

118
00:10:53,527 --> 00:10:56,238
Thank you.

119
00:11:00,618 --> 00:11:01,452
You must

120
00:11:02,787 --> 00:11:03,871
dismiss Geun-won.

121
00:11:06,248 --> 00:11:08,167
The accident that killed Mr. Park
ten years ago

122
00:11:08,959 --> 00:11:10,836
and the stuff you did to cover that up.

123
00:11:12,171 --> 00:11:14,757
If people find out what happened,
you'll get involved in that mess.

124
00:11:17,176 --> 00:11:18,219
And if that happens,

125
00:11:19,178 --> 00:11:20,930
it'll no longer be a family issue.

126
00:11:27,603 --> 00:11:28,646
How do you know

127
00:11:30,314 --> 00:11:31,732
about what happened back then?

128
00:11:39,156 --> 00:11:41,534
That kid, Yi-seo,
uploaded what she recorded.

129
00:11:43,327 --> 00:11:44,995
Geun-won had just graduated high school.

130
00:11:46,247 --> 00:11:48,124
He couldn't have dealt with it alone.

131
00:11:53,379 --> 00:11:54,672
Is it the company or your son?

132
00:11:57,466 --> 00:11:58,551
You need to choose.

133
00:12:24,368 --> 00:12:26,704
Seung-kwon, I'll clean the bathroom.

134
00:12:26,787 --> 00:12:29,039
Here. Gosh, what's this?

135
00:12:29,540 --> 00:12:30,583
Go ahead.

136
00:12:39,758 --> 00:12:40,593
Boss.

137
00:12:42,678 --> 00:12:45,222
I knew something happened
between you and Geun-soo's family.

138
00:12:45,306 --> 00:12:47,683
But this is a lot more serious
than what I had imagined.

139
00:12:48,350 --> 00:12:50,436
It would've been nice if you told us.

140
00:12:50,519 --> 00:12:52,229
We don't know how to react to this.

141
00:12:53,063 --> 00:12:54,815
-What should we do?
-What's there to ask?

142
00:12:55,483 --> 00:12:58,486
Hyun-yi, you keep making good food
while Seung-kwon serves the tables.

143
00:13:01,197 --> 00:13:02,323
Yi-seo is right.

144
00:13:02,406 --> 00:13:04,366
None of that matters. Just focus on work.

145
00:13:05,451 --> 00:13:06,785
-Okay.
-Okay.

146
00:13:13,918 --> 00:13:15,419
LEE HO-JIN

147
00:13:18,172 --> 00:13:19,924
Hey. Right now?

148
00:13:20,758 --> 00:13:22,134
I have time. Why?

149
00:13:27,306 --> 00:13:28,891
Okay, ma'am.

150
00:13:28,974 --> 00:13:30,476
I think it'll be fine.

151
00:13:33,896 --> 00:13:34,897
Hello.

152
00:13:39,151 --> 00:13:40,402
This is important.

153
00:13:41,028 --> 00:13:43,322
Yes, I thought she should also hear it.

154
00:13:44,198 --> 00:13:45,366
Let's sit down.

155
00:13:52,665 --> 00:13:55,084
I wanted to introduce her to you one day.

156
00:13:55,960 --> 00:13:58,295
I'm Jo Yi-seo, the manager of DanBam.

157
00:13:59,046 --> 00:14:00,631
I saw you at Chairman Jang's seminar.

158
00:14:02,424 --> 00:14:03,342
You're the one

159
00:14:04,510 --> 00:14:06,595
who uploaded
Geun-won's confession on the web.

160
00:14:07,263 --> 00:14:08,264
Yes, ma'am.

161
00:14:08,347 --> 00:14:11,725
I know I'm working with Saeroyi right now.

162
00:14:12,768 --> 00:14:14,270
But I'm a director at Jangga Co.

163
00:14:14,853 --> 00:14:16,564
Do you know how much our stock price

164
00:14:16,730 --> 00:14:18,649
has plummeted because of you?

165
00:14:20,359 --> 00:14:21,318
But that was

166
00:14:22,319 --> 00:14:23,654
bound to happen one day.

167
00:14:26,448 --> 00:14:27,992
-What?
-She's right.

168
00:14:28,701 --> 00:14:31,245
Yi-seo and I already talked about that.

169
00:14:32,288 --> 00:14:33,497
What do you mean?

170
00:14:34,290 --> 00:14:36,500
Chairman Jang represents Jangga Co.

171
00:14:36,792 --> 00:14:39,044
What do you think will happen
to the stock price

172
00:14:39,128 --> 00:14:41,297
once you replace Chairman Jang

173
00:14:41,797 --> 00:14:43,173
and become the chairwoman?

174
00:14:44,633 --> 00:14:47,595
You're very straightforward for a kid.
What's your point?

175
00:14:48,888 --> 00:14:50,931
I think now is your chance.

176
00:14:54,268 --> 00:14:57,605
The stock price plummeted
because of Chairman Jang's family issues.

177
00:14:58,063 --> 00:15:00,566
This already happened in the past,
and it's happening again.

178
00:15:01,233 --> 00:15:04,528
What do you think the stockholders
are thinking right now?

179
00:15:05,905 --> 00:15:08,407
This is probably what's going on
in their minds.

180
00:15:09,658 --> 00:15:13,037
"This family doesn't deserve
to lead Jangga Co."

181
00:15:20,377 --> 00:15:21,962
-Are you saying--
-Yes.

182
00:15:24,381 --> 00:15:25,633
Now is the right time

183
00:15:26,634 --> 00:15:27,760
to dismiss the chairman.

184
00:15:40,022 --> 00:15:41,148
What do you think?

185
00:15:45,110 --> 00:15:46,904
I think it's more than possible.

186
00:15:52,493 --> 00:15:53,410
Keep going.

187
00:15:54,411 --> 00:15:56,372
But like I said earlier,

188
00:15:56,455 --> 00:15:58,332
Chairman Jang represents Jangga Co.

189
00:15:59,333 --> 00:16:01,669
There's too much at risk
to recklessly start a fight.

190
00:16:01,752 --> 00:16:04,338
If things go haywire,
it'll end up destroying you instead.

191
00:16:05,339 --> 00:16:08,050
So first of all,
we need to satisfy two conditions.

192
00:16:08,634 --> 00:16:09,635
"Two conditions"?

193
00:16:10,970 --> 00:16:12,596
The recording went public,

194
00:16:12,680 --> 00:16:14,556
but it still doesn't have
much legal force.

195
00:16:15,140 --> 00:16:17,059
He didn't even get charged
for what he did.

196
00:16:18,060 --> 00:16:19,228
Here's the first condition.

197
00:16:37,663 --> 00:16:39,331
Dad, why aren't you eating?

198
00:16:44,378 --> 00:16:45,379
Hye-won.

199
00:16:48,966 --> 00:16:50,759
I need to tell you something.

200
00:16:53,637 --> 00:16:54,847
A long time ago,

201
00:16:56,515 --> 00:16:58,308
I did something really bad

202
00:16:59,893 --> 00:17:01,020
to Saeroyi.

203
00:17:08,485 --> 00:17:10,654
You didn't have to come with me.

204
00:17:11,697 --> 00:17:14,158
My life depends on this.
It's right that I come with you.

205
00:17:18,912 --> 00:17:19,955
Isn't he...

206
00:17:28,630 --> 00:17:29,506
Detective.

207
00:17:31,175 --> 00:17:32,593
Hey, Saeroyi.

208
00:17:33,969 --> 00:17:35,012
What's the matter?

209
00:17:37,014 --> 00:17:38,891
The thing is, Hye-won...

210
00:17:40,768 --> 00:17:41,685
What?

211
00:17:43,187 --> 00:17:44,229
Hye-won!

212
00:17:47,232 --> 00:17:48,233
Hye-won!

213
00:17:53,655 --> 00:17:54,656
Hye-won!

214
00:17:56,116 --> 00:17:57,076
My gosh.

215
00:17:57,743 --> 00:18:00,287
Why does she disappear all the time?

216
00:18:01,121 --> 00:18:02,164
Hye-won!

217
00:18:03,415 --> 00:18:04,249
Hye-won!

218
00:18:09,505 --> 00:18:10,339
My gosh...

219
00:18:11,340 --> 00:18:12,591
I think she was too startled.

220
00:18:17,846 --> 00:18:19,014
I made up my mind

221
00:18:19,723 --> 00:18:20,766
to turn myself in.

222
00:18:23,018 --> 00:18:24,603
And I bet she was really disappointed.

223
00:18:25,145 --> 00:18:26,438
Gosh.

224
00:18:27,064 --> 00:18:28,565
She ran out while I was talking.

225
00:18:31,193 --> 00:18:32,111
Hye-won!

226
00:18:33,362 --> 00:18:34,404
Hye-won!

227
00:18:40,536 --> 00:18:41,912
Hye-won!

228
00:18:43,539 --> 00:18:44,540
My goodness.

229
00:18:48,418 --> 00:18:50,838
Hey! Kid!

230
00:18:55,300 --> 00:18:56,343
Hye-won.

231
00:19:02,432 --> 00:19:03,433
Hello...

232
00:19:04,518 --> 00:19:06,895
My gosh, you practically made me exercise.

233
00:19:07,521 --> 00:19:10,816
Why would you run away from home?
You're just an elementary school kid.

234
00:19:17,447 --> 00:19:18,490
Hye-won!

235
00:19:21,869 --> 00:19:22,828
Hye-won.

236
00:19:34,506 --> 00:19:35,674
What my dad did

237
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:38,927
to Saeroyi's dad...

238
00:19:40,637 --> 00:19:43,140
He shouldn't have done that as a cop.

239
00:19:44,683 --> 00:19:47,019
I feel really sorry about what happened.

240
00:19:50,939 --> 00:19:52,566
Are you disappointed in your dad?

241
00:19:53,275 --> 00:19:54,985
Yes. But...

242
00:19:56,278 --> 00:19:59,072
Saeroyi, I'm sorry for saying this.

243
00:20:00,574 --> 00:20:02,534
But I don't want my dad
to get punished either.

244
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:04,828
I don't want him to leave me.

245
00:20:10,500 --> 00:20:12,836
I bet your dad's been
having a hard time as well.

246
00:20:14,171 --> 00:20:15,172
Just like you,

247
00:20:15,756 --> 00:20:17,424
he didn't want to be apart from you.

248
00:20:18,717 --> 00:20:19,843
Everyone

249
00:20:20,677 --> 00:20:22,095
makes mistakes.

250
00:20:22,888 --> 00:20:24,806
But not everyone takes responsibility.

251
00:20:24,890 --> 00:20:26,475
Only the brave can do that.

252
00:20:29,519 --> 00:20:32,564
You told me that you're proud
of your dad, right?

253
00:20:34,608 --> 00:20:35,567
Yes.

254
00:20:36,818 --> 00:20:40,781
Your dad mustered up his courage
and decided to take responsibility

255
00:20:41,573 --> 00:20:44,660
so he could be the proud dad
that you think he is.

256
00:20:46,203 --> 00:20:47,955
So why don't you try and understand him?

257
00:20:57,047 --> 00:20:58,382
Dad.

258
00:21:05,597 --> 00:21:06,598
Hye-won.

259
00:21:12,938 --> 00:21:14,439
I'm sorry.

260
00:21:15,732 --> 00:21:16,775
I'm sorry.

261
00:21:21,530 --> 00:21:22,739
From now on,

262
00:21:24,032 --> 00:21:25,325
I'll be an honorable person.

263
00:21:26,076 --> 00:21:27,202
So please don't cry.

264
00:21:28,245 --> 00:21:29,496
Here's the first condition.

265
00:21:30,080 --> 00:21:31,873
Jang Geun-won needs to get charged.

266
00:21:32,874 --> 00:21:36,336
And in order for that to happen,
Detective Oh needs to turn himself in.

267
00:21:41,341 --> 00:21:43,927
Don't cry.

268
00:21:46,054 --> 00:21:47,180
He's here!

269
00:21:54,354 --> 00:21:56,523
Mr. Jang, did you really cover up
a hit-and-run accident?

270
00:21:56,606 --> 00:21:57,899
How do you feel?

