00:42:06,232 --> 00:42:07,566
You should get going.

535
00:42:12,112 --> 00:42:14,073
Mr. Kim, give him a ride.

536
00:42:16,158 --> 00:42:17,243
Yes, sir.

537
00:42:21,205 --> 00:42:22,706
I'll see you later.

538
00:42:26,168 --> 00:42:27,253
Dad.

539
00:42:30,422 --> 00:42:31,507
Hang in there.

540
00:42:52,319 --> 00:42:53,696
Let's get going then.

541
00:42:55,030 --> 00:42:56,031
Pardon?

542
00:42:57,741 --> 00:42:59,827
We still have four hours left.

543
00:43:29,815 --> 00:43:31,525
How dare you come here?

544
00:43:33,861 --> 00:43:36,405
I'm here to cast a vote as a shareholder.

545
00:43:37,239 --> 00:43:38,824
To have Chairman Jang dismissed.

546
00:43:40,242 --> 00:43:41,660
You jerk.

547
00:43:45,289 --> 00:43:46,498
Thank you.

548
00:43:49,710 --> 00:43:51,253
I couldn't see the end of it.

549
00:43:52,546 --> 00:43:54,340
But thanks to you, it seems possible.

550
00:43:56,592 --> 00:43:58,510
Park Saeroyi!

551
00:43:59,261 --> 00:44:00,179
Director Jang.

552
00:44:00,888 --> 00:44:02,806
You can't make things worse here.

553
00:44:04,933 --> 00:44:06,268
We don't have time. Let's go.

554
00:44:15,152 --> 00:44:18,072
We're not someone you can deal with.

555
00:44:18,656 --> 00:44:19,573
Me

556
00:44:20,282 --> 00:44:21,700
and my dad.

557
00:44:22,993 --> 00:44:24,244
Go ahead and get your own way.

558
00:44:25,371 --> 00:44:26,580
And see if it works.

559
00:44:49,645 --> 00:44:51,397
I can't calm myself down.

560
00:44:52,523 --> 00:44:55,150
When does the shareholders' meeting begin?

561
00:44:55,776 --> 00:44:56,985
In three hours.

562
00:44:58,362 --> 00:45:01,490
Gosh. I'm glad Geun-soo is off today.

563
00:45:02,116 --> 00:45:03,534
No matter how the result turns out,

564
00:45:04,034 --> 00:45:06,412
I don't know how to react in front of him.

565
00:45:07,329 --> 00:45:10,541
Boss said before. You don't have to do
things you don't mean.

566
00:45:10,624 --> 00:45:12,042
I'm just being considerate.

567
00:45:12,876 --> 00:45:16,046
Both Saeroyi and you are so brutal.

568
00:45:16,130 --> 00:45:18,549
Hey, guys. Hang on.

569
00:45:20,426 --> 00:45:21,760
Look at this.

570
00:45:28,684 --> 00:45:31,103
I SINCERELY APOLOGIZE FOR ALL THE TROUBLE

571
00:45:34,189 --> 00:45:36,316
PRESS CONFERENCE OF CHAIRMAN JANG DAE-HEE

572
00:45:54,543 --> 00:45:57,004
Thank you all

573
00:45:59,006 --> 00:46:01,300
for coming all the way here.
I'm Jang Dae-hee.

574
00:46:04,261 --> 00:46:05,554
Today,

575
00:46:07,514 --> 00:46:09,641
I'm here as a father of a son,

576
00:46:10,559 --> 00:46:12,394
not as the chairman...

577
00:46:12,478 --> 00:46:13,479
URGENT PRESS CONFERENCE

578
00:46:13,562 --> 00:46:15,022
...of Jangga Co.

579
00:46:17,316 --> 00:46:18,942
A press conference?

580
00:46:20,319 --> 00:46:21,528
That old codger.

581
00:46:23,322 --> 00:46:24,573
What is he up to?

582
00:46:26,325 --> 00:46:27,451
First of all,

583
00:46:28,118 --> 00:46:30,996
I'm sorry for all the trouble
my son has caused.

584
00:46:31,830 --> 00:46:32,998
As his father...

585
00:46:33,707 --> 00:46:34,666
Dad.

586
00:46:34,750 --> 00:46:37,002
I didn't discipline my son
in the right way.

587
00:46:38,086 --> 00:46:39,880
I deeply regret it

588
00:46:40,464 --> 00:46:41,965
and apologize.

589
00:46:55,646 --> 00:46:56,772
My son

590
00:46:58,607 --> 00:47:02,027
is suspected of a hit-and-run accident
from ten years ago,

591
00:47:04,279 --> 00:47:06,323
so he's being questioned by prosecutors.

592
00:47:07,574 --> 00:47:09,451
According to our attorney,

593
00:47:10,160 --> 00:47:12,746
there's not enough physical
and circumstantial evidence

594
00:47:13,539 --> 00:47:15,415
against him.

595
00:47:17,000 --> 00:47:17,918
So my son is

596
00:47:21,004 --> 00:47:22,589
going to be found not guilty.

597
00:47:23,507 --> 00:47:26,260
He will never be able
to win the shareholders over like that.

598
00:47:26,843 --> 00:47:28,470
He's totally mistaken.

599
00:47:29,888 --> 00:47:31,932
A few days ago, when my son came back

600
00:47:32,015 --> 00:47:34,059
from the first prosecutor's investigation,

601
00:47:34,643 --> 00:47:35,519
I...

602
00:47:42,568 --> 00:47:43,902
I heard it

603
00:47:47,698 --> 00:47:48,991
from my son.

604
00:47:51,702 --> 00:47:53,954
The hit-and-run accident
from ten years ago

605
00:48:00,127 --> 00:48:01,920
was his doing.

606
00:48:08,302 --> 00:48:09,761
We're doomed.

607
00:48:31,908 --> 00:48:35,037
With the money I trusted him with,

608
00:48:35,996 --> 00:48:39,541
he hired someone else...

609
00:48:39,625 --> 00:48:40,751
Pull over.

610
00:48:42,878 --> 00:48:45,130
...to take the fault.

611
00:48:45,213 --> 00:48:47,049
CHAIRMAN JANG ADMITS HIS SON'S GUILT

612
00:48:49,009 --> 00:48:50,427
Did you not hear me?

613
00:48:51,219 --> 00:48:52,596
I told you to pull over.

614
00:48:52,679 --> 00:48:55,265
I was ordered to drive you
to the Public Prosecutors' Office.

615
00:49:02,814 --> 00:49:04,650
I couldn't believe my ears.

616
00:49:06,109 --> 00:49:07,152
That day,

617
00:49:08,487 --> 00:49:11,156
I looked into the case immediately

618
00:49:12,491 --> 00:49:13,617
and found out

619
00:49:15,327 --> 00:49:16,828
what my son said was true.

620
00:49:50,570 --> 00:49:52,823
Damn it.

621
00:49:55,784 --> 00:49:56,785
What?

622
00:49:57,160 --> 00:49:58,620
I am solely to blame for it.

623
00:49:59,329 --> 00:50:01,832
I was so preoccupied
with running the company

624
00:50:01,915 --> 00:50:04,126
that I failed to discipline my son.

625
00:50:07,003 --> 00:50:08,547
It's all my fault.

626
00:50:10,382 --> 00:50:12,592
What am I supposed
to do for my son's sake?

627
00:50:14,636 --> 00:50:16,805
What is the right thing to do as a father?

628
00:50:17,973 --> 00:50:19,224
I'm a foolish father.

629
00:50:20,225 --> 00:50:23,520
I hesitated
even after finding out the truth.

630
00:50:24,980 --> 00:50:26,982
But feeling desperate,

631
00:50:27,816 --> 00:50:30,152
as soon as it turned out to be true,

632
00:50:33,613 --> 00:50:37,075
I took all the evidence
to the prosecution.

633
00:50:37,492 --> 00:50:39,453
Is it possible that he didn't know?

634
00:50:40,579 --> 00:50:42,080
How is it even possible?

635
00:50:43,665 --> 00:50:45,959
That's the last thing I can do

636
00:50:48,253 --> 00:50:50,297
as a foolish father.

637
00:50:51,840 --> 00:50:53,175
He must pay

638
00:50:56,094 --> 00:50:57,846
for the crime he committed.

639
00:51:14,362 --> 00:51:17,824
To the victim who passed away
because of my son

640
00:51:19,201 --> 00:51:20,660
and his family,

641
00:51:21,870 --> 00:51:23,872
I sincerely apologize.

642
00:51:24,790 --> 00:51:26,166
We will

643
00:51:27,918 --> 00:51:29,878
regret it for the rest of our lives.

644
00:51:30,587 --> 00:51:31,963
I'm sorry.

645
00:51:32,672 --> 00:51:34,716
I'm deeply sorry.

646
00:51:35,467 --> 00:51:36,301
I'm sorry.

647
00:51:39,179 --> 00:51:40,138
I sincerely apologize.

648
00:51:42,891 --> 00:51:44,726
I'm terribly sorry.

649
00:51:55,946 --> 00:51:57,155
What's going on?

650
00:52:09,918 --> 00:52:12,420
-He's here.
-There he is.

651
00:52:13,547 --> 00:52:15,882
-Where is your son?
-Is it true your son did it?

652
00:52:16,383 --> 00:52:17,926
Are you not involved in the case?

653
00:52:18,009 --> 00:52:19,427
What are your plans for the future?

654
00:52:19,511 --> 00:52:21,555
Do the prosecutors know about this?

655
00:52:21,638 --> 00:52:23,723
-Please say a word.
-Please answer it, sir.

656
00:52:23,807 --> 00:52:26,351
-Please tell us.
-Chairman Jang.

657
00:52:26,434 --> 00:52:28,520
-Hang on.
-Say something before you leave.

658
00:52:29,020 --> 00:52:30,939
-Please answer the question.
-Chairman Jang.

659
00:52:31,022 --> 00:52:32,691
Let me ask you one more question.

660
00:52:32,774 --> 00:52:35,068
-How are you feeling now?
-What are you going to do?

661
00:52:35,151 --> 00:52:37,320
-There's Jang Geun-won.
-What?

662
00:52:37,404 --> 00:52:38,697
-Where?
-There he is.

663
00:52:39,531 --> 00:52:41,575
-Please say a word.
-Is it all true?

664
00:52:41,658 --> 00:52:44,661
-How are you feeling now?
-It's your father who reported you.

665
00:52:44,744 --> 00:52:47,747
-Is what he said all true?
-How do you feel?

666
00:52:48,331 --> 00:52:49,708
Were you alone in this?

667
00:52:49,791 --> 00:52:51,877
Please say a word.

668
00:52:57,257 --> 00:52:58,842
As your dad,

669
00:52:59,426 --> 00:53:03,305
I've never given you a warm hug even once.

670
00:53:10,395 --> 00:53:11,563
Is what your father said true?

671
00:53:11,646 --> 00:53:14,316
Your father reported you
to the prosecution.

672
00:53:14,399 --> 00:53:17,152
How are you feeling now?
Did you do it all alone?

673
00:53:17,235 --> 00:53:18,945
Is your father not involved in the case?

674
00:53:19,029 --> 00:53:20,864
Please answer the question.

675
00:54:20,507 --> 00:54:22,008
Please answer the question.

676
00:54:26,346 --> 00:54:27,263
It's

677
00:54:30,183 --> 00:54:31,685
all my fault.

678
00:54:31,768 --> 00:54:34,270
-Is it all correct?
-Wasn't your father involved?

679
00:54:34,354 --> 00:54:37,065
-Do you admit the charge?
-How do you feel about your father?

680
00:54:49,077 --> 00:54:50,203
Therefore,

681
00:54:54,499 --> 00:54:56,710
the dismissal of the chairman

682
00:55:03,258 --> 00:55:04,759
is rejected.

683
00:55:21,026 --> 00:55:22,652
So we've fallen out with each other,

684
00:55:23,695 --> 00:55:25,238
but I have no grudge against you.

685
00:55:25,905 --> 00:55:29,200
I believe you did
the whole thing for Jangga Co.

686
00:55:36,708 --> 00:55:37,876
Have some.

687
00:55:38,585 --> 00:55:42,088
She makes really good tea.

688
00:55:42,630 --> 00:55:45,175
Oh, right. It's you who planted her.
I guess you know it already.

689
00:55:53,266 --> 00:55:54,392
Chairman Jang.

690
00:55:55,685 --> 00:55:57,270
You may leave.

691
00:56:04,110 --> 00:56:05,904
When did you find out?

692
00:56:07,739 --> 00:56:11,367
I thought you knew that I'd been prying.

693
00:56:13,244 --> 00:56:15,330
You should've been more cautious.

694
00:56:16,289 --> 00:56:18,041
That was very clumsy of you.

695
00:56:20,335 --> 00:56:22,754
You just ended up getting paid back.

696
00:56:30,929 --> 00:56:32,097
You must be disappointed.

697
00:56:34,390 --> 00:56:36,059
Not really.

698
00:56:38,311 --> 00:56:40,855
I just didn't know you were that good.

699
00:56:44,818 --> 00:56:46,611
It's not that I have grudge against you,

700
00:56:47,779 --> 00:56:49,823
but I'm quite disappointed.

701
00:56:49,906 --> 00:56:51,866
I can't kick you out though.

702
00:56:53,118 --> 00:56:55,495
I will be too ashamed to face Bo-hyeon.

703
00:57:03,378 --> 00:57:05,505
What are you going to do?

704
00:57:08,091 --> 00:57:09,717
I'll transfer you to the Pajin office

705
00:57:11,427 --> 00:57:12,762
so you can clear your head.

706
00:57:30,280 --> 00:57:32,657
JANGGA PUB

707
00:57:38,288 --> 00:57:39,581
Hey, my partner.

708
00:57:39,664 --> 00:57:40,832
Over here.

709
00:57:40,915 --> 00:57:41,916
Hey.

710
00:57:42,000 --> 00:57:43,960
Come have a seat.

711
00:57:45,920 --> 00:57:47,046
I call you my partner,

712
00:57:47,130 --> 00:57:49,340
but we didn't even get to drink once.

713
00:57:49,924 --> 00:57:50,925
Here.

714
00:57:51,426 --> 00:57:52,677
Let me pour you a drink.

715
00:57:56,973 --> 00:57:58,933
I'm sorry. I didn't read it right.

716
00:57:59,017 --> 00:58:01,769
That just kills my appetite.
I told you to stop.

717
00:58:10,987 --> 00:58:12,280
What are you going to do now?

718
00:58:12,363 --> 00:58:13,740
I have no choice.

719
00:58:15,158 --> 00:58:17,577
All my people are kicked out.

720
00:58:21,331 --> 00:58:22,999
And I'll be banished.

721
00:58:23,416 --> 00:58:24,751
I'm sorry, Director Kang.

722
00:58:24,834 --> 00:58:28,463
Gosh, that's enough. Will you please stop?

723
00:58:41,267 --> 00:58:43,353
I need to go to the restroom.

724
00:58:44,562 --> 00:58:45,855
I'm sorry.

725
00:58:49,317 --> 00:58:51,361
It was my decision.

726
00:58:51,486 --> 00:58:53,863
What is he sorry for?

727
00:58:56,908 --> 00:58:58,201
So

728
00:58:58,910 --> 00:59:00,995
what are you going to do now?

729
00:59:02,872 --> 00:59:04,582
I will have to come up with another way.

730
00:59:04,666 --> 00:59:06,334
Another way?

731
00:59:08,503 --> 00:59:09,504
You mean Chairman Jang?

732
00:59:16,386 --> 00:59:17,387
Yes.

733
00:59:22,642 --> 00:59:25,728
Are you not going to give up
even after ruining the whole thing?

734
00:59:26,729 --> 00:59:27,855
I'm not giving up.

735
00:59:32,819 --> 00:59:34,445
How could I give up?

736
00:59:36,322 --> 00:59:38,616
The odds are stacked against you.

737
00:59:44,706 --> 00:59:46,791
The odds weren't with me
when I was a penniless ex-con

738
00:59:46,874 --> 00:59:48,626
and a high school dropout.

739
00:59:49,294 --> 00:59:52,547
I met a crushing defeat this time,

740
00:59:53,131 --> 00:59:55,216
but Jang Geun-won will pay for his crime,

741
00:59:55,300 --> 00:59:57,218
and Chairman Jang has lost his son.

742
00:59:58,469 --> 01:00:01,806
I see. I lost everything though.

743
01:00:02,807 --> 01:00:04,642
I'm a little sad.

744
01:00:07,937 --> 01:00:08,938
Right.

745
01:00:10,148 --> 01:00:13,234
Actually, it's you who lost. Not me.

746
01:00:14,110 --> 01:00:15,236
I'm sorry.

747
01:00:20,241 --> 01:00:21,868
So I will keep on going.

748
01:00:28,541 --> 01:00:30,376
Like I said before,

749
01:00:31,586 --> 01:00:33,338
you're such a jerk.

750
01:00:41,179 --> 01:00:42,263
This watch.

751
01:00:42,764 --> 01:00:44,599
It belonged to Mr. Park.

752
01:00:45,767 --> 01:00:46,768
Right.

753
01:00:47,226 --> 01:00:49,395
I wear this when I have
something important to do.

754
01:00:53,858 --> 01:00:55,902
The 1997 IMF financial crisis.

755
01:00:55,985 --> 01:00:57,487
Jangga was in crisis. I mean,

756
01:00:58,696 --> 01:01:00,740
the whole nation was facing a huge crisis.

757
01:01:01,532 --> 01:01:05,203
And there was this dish
that saved Jangga Co. from the crisis.

758
01:01:07,580 --> 01:01:08,456
This one.

759
01:01:09,624 --> 01:01:12,669
The spicy pork with gochujang.

760
01:01:13,503 --> 01:01:15,213
I read it from the autobiography.

761
01:01:15,546 --> 01:01:18,132
It's the signature menu of Jangga Co.
developed by Chairman Jang.

762
01:01:18,841 --> 01:01:21,928
I heard it's made Jangga Co.
what it is now.

763
01:01:23,012 --> 01:01:24,013
Right.

764
01:01:24,972 --> 01:01:26,933
It's not too far-fetched to say

765
01:01:30,978 --> 01:01:34,565
that Jangga Co. wouldn't have come
this far without this special sauce.

766
01:01:36,818 --> 01:01:39,821
Marketing always needs a good story.

767
01:01:40,488 --> 01:01:44,200
It's just more compelling to say

768
01:01:44,283 --> 01:01:48,121
that it was developed by the chairman,

769
01:01:48,621 --> 01:01:51,207
not a mere employee.

770
01:01:53,626 --> 01:01:54,627
What?

771
01:01:56,838 --> 01:01:59,132
It's Mr. Park who made the sauce.

772
01:01:59,674 --> 01:02:01,676
It's the dish developed by Mr. Park.

773
01:02:04,804 --> 01:02:08,307
And what he got in return
for giving credit to the chairman

774
01:02:09,142 --> 01:02:10,601
is this watch.

775
01:02:20,194 --> 01:02:21,529
Mr. Park...

776
01:02:22,029 --> 01:02:25,867
He should have been the last person
to be kicked out from Jangga like that.

777
01:02:31,956 --> 01:02:34,876
Like you said,
I'm the only one who lost this time.

778
01:02:35,752 --> 01:02:38,546
I just gave up so easily after one defeat.

779
01:02:39,172 --> 01:02:40,965
I bet you'll be a lot better than me.

780
01:02:44,177 --> 01:02:45,303
Director Kang.

781
01:02:46,053 --> 01:02:47,555
Give me your hand.

782
01:02:48,431 --> 01:02:49,348
What?

783
01:03:01,986 --> 01:03:03,821
I've passed the baton.

784
01:03:07,492 --> 01:03:10,161
Make sure to win, Saeroyi.

785
01:03:23,758 --> 01:03:27,470
The defendant was aware
that the victim was injured,

786
01:03:27,553 --> 01:03:29,430
but he ran away without rescue actions.

787
01:03:29,514 --> 01:03:32,016
Also, even after he learned
that the victim had died,

788
01:03:32,099 --> 01:03:33,392
he hired someone else

789
01:03:33,476 --> 01:03:36,187
to make a false statement
and cover up the case

790
01:03:36,270 --> 01:03:39,106
without turning himself in.

791
01:03:39,190 --> 01:03:42,109
He has shown no remorse for his crime,

792
01:03:42,193 --> 01:03:43,945
and the nature of the crime
is very serious.

793
01:03:44,320 --> 01:03:48,282
According to Article 54, Section 1
of the Road Traffic Act

794
01:03:48,574 --> 01:03:50,785
and Article 5, Section 3

795
01:03:50,868 --> 01:03:53,871
of the Additional Punishment Law
on Specific Crimes,

796
01:03:53,955 --> 01:03:56,833
the defendant is sentenced
to seven years in prison.

797
01:04:34,036 --> 01:04:35,413
You must be satisfied.

798
01:04:45,423 --> 01:04:46,549
Not at all.

799
01:04:47,466 --> 01:04:49,719
You're sitting comfortably right there.

800
01:05:01,981 --> 01:05:02,982
All right.

801
01:05:03,566 --> 01:05:06,736
Having Min-jung on your side
was a fine choice.

802
01:05:07,862 --> 01:05:10,740
But Jangga Co. won't fall apart so easily.

803
01:05:12,658 --> 01:05:13,910
I want to ask you.

804
01:05:15,494 --> 01:05:18,873
Is it something you want to protect
even giving up on your own son?

805
01:05:20,708 --> 01:05:21,918
I mean Jangga Co.

806
01:05:22,877 --> 01:05:26,714
For Jangga Co.,
I'm willing to do anything.

807
01:05:28,174 --> 01:05:29,717
But you know what?

808
01:05:31,594 --> 01:05:33,304
I still feel quite bitter.

809
01:05:33,387 --> 01:05:35,306
He's just paying for what he did.

810
01:05:40,478 --> 01:05:42,480
You're crossing way over the line.

811
01:05:44,440 --> 01:05:47,026
You haven't paid for what you did yet.

812
01:05:48,194 --> 01:05:49,195
You are

813
01:05:51,113 --> 01:05:52,573
coming up next.

814
01:05:55,409 --> 01:05:56,869
You told me before.

815
01:05:57,703 --> 01:05:59,580
That I'm your enemy.

816
01:06:01,499 --> 01:06:03,751
Fine. I admit it.

817
01:06:05,127 --> 01:06:06,921
I, Jang Dae-hee,

818
01:06:08,589 --> 01:06:10,466
have you for an enemy.

819
01:06:13,177 --> 01:06:14,178
I will

820
01:06:15,221 --> 01:06:17,181
make you regret this.

821
01:06:20,434 --> 01:06:21,435
I will

822
01:06:24,271 --> 01:06:26,065
offer my life

823
01:06:27,858 --> 01:06:29,485
to make the same promise.

824
01:06:54,301 --> 01:06:56,095
It's so close by.

825
01:06:57,888 --> 01:06:59,765
But I couldn't come to see you even once.

826
01:07:04,645 --> 01:07:06,856
I'm a horrible son who went to jail

827
01:07:08,232 --> 01:07:10,234
without finishing your funeral.

828
01:07:13,070 --> 01:07:14,530
I felt too bad

829
01:07:18,242 --> 01:07:19,702
to come see you.

830
01:07:24,290 --> 01:07:27,585
PARK SUNG-YEOL

831
01:07:32,256 --> 01:07:37,595
JANG GEUN-WON OF JANGGA CO. WHO TRIED TO
COVER UP HIS MURDER ENDS UP IN PRISON

832
01:07:51,025 --> 01:07:52,902
I was such a bad son,

833
01:07:55,988 --> 01:07:58,115
but I have a lot of good people around me.

834
01:08:03,245 --> 01:08:05,456
You must've been worried leaving me alone.

835
01:08:36,654 --> 01:08:38,239
But you don't have to worry anymore.

836
01:08:39,281 --> 01:08:40,407
Please rest in peace.

837
01:09:01,303 --> 01:09:02,805
How does it taste?

838
01:09:11,480 --> 01:09:12,481
My son.

839
01:09:26,287 --> 01:09:27,288
It's still...

840
01:09:32,626 --> 01:09:33,836
bitter.

841
01:10:08,162 --> 01:10:10,080
I'll leave DanBam.

842
01:10:10,164 --> 01:10:11,707
You've been holding out well.

843
01:10:11,790 --> 01:10:13,375
Why do you want to quit now?

844
01:10:13,459 --> 01:10:15,794
I will live with greed.

845
01:10:15,878 --> 01:10:18,130
It's nice to meet you, Mr. Oh.

846
01:10:18,214 --> 01:10:21,342
It's too soon to attract investment
to start something.

847
01:10:21,425 --> 01:10:23,677
-When will we catch up with Jangga Co.?
-Yi-Seo.

848
01:10:23,761 --> 01:10:26,305
Did you have feelings for Yi-seo before?

849
01:10:26,805 --> 01:10:29,099
You're a smart girl.
Why are you acting like a kid?

850
01:10:29,183 --> 01:10:30,351
I love you.

851
01:10:30,851 --> 01:10:32,269
I really love you.

852
01:10:40,110 --> 01:10:42,112
